messages.content: What is the purpose of the 'Image(s) to Websocket (Base64)' node in ComfyUI?

The 'Image(s) to Websocket (Base64)' node in ComfyUI accepts a batch of image tensors and returns an array of base64 encoded images using the websocket. It also returns a string (Actions) for routing.
What does the 'Load Image (Base64)' node in ComfyUI do?
The 'Load Image (Base64)' node in ComfyUI accepts a base64 encoded image and returns an image tensor and mask.
What is the function of the 'Load Images (Base64)' node in ComfyUI?
The 'Load Images (Base64)' node in ComfyUI accepts a string with a specific structure and returns a batch of image tensors and masks.
What is the structure of the input string for the 'Load Images (Base64)' node in ComfyUI?
The input string for the 'Load Images (Base64)' node in ComfyUI should have the following structure: 0x4(Image count) 0x8(Image1 length) Image1(base64) ... 0x8(ImageN length) ImageN(base64).
How many nodes are described in the given text about Knodes in ComfyUI?
The given text describes 3 nodes in ComfyUI related to Knodes.
Do the nodes in the given text work with base64 encoded images?
Yes, all three nodes described in the given text work with base64 encoded images in some capacity.
Which node in the given text returns a string for routing?
The 'Image(s) to Websocket (Base64)' node in ComfyUI returns a string (Actions) for routing.
